#. type: Content of: <guide><title>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:6
#, no-wrap
msgid "Gentoo Linux nVidia Guide"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><abstract>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:22
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Many Gentooists have an nVidia chipset on their system. nVidia provides specific\n"
"Linux drivers to boost the performance of your card. This guide informs you how\n"
"to install and configure these drivers.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:35
#, no-wrap
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:40
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The nVidia drivers in the tree are released by nVidia and are built against the\n"
"Linux kernel. They contain a binary blob that does the heavy lifting for talking\n"
"to the card. The drivers consist of two parts, a kernel module, and an X11\n"
"driver. Both parts are included in a single package. Due to the way nVidia has\n"
"been packaging their drivers, you will need to make some choices before you\n"
"install the drivers.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:49
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The <c>nvidia-drivers</c> package contains the latest drivers from nVidia with\n"
"support for <e>all</e> cards, with several versions available depending on how\n"
"old your card is. It uses an eclass to detect what kind of card you're running\n"
"so that it installs the proper version.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:60
#, no-wrap
msgid "Driver compatibility"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:62
#, no-wrap
msgid "Which version?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:66
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The <c>nvidia-drivers</c> package supports the full range of available nVidia\n"
"cards. Multiple versions are available for installation, depending on the\n"
"card(s) you have.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:72
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Newer cards such as the GeForce 400, 300, 200, 100, 9, 8, 7, and 6 series should\n"
"use the latest drivers.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:77
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Older cards such as the GeForce FX 5 series should use the 173.x drivers, such\n"
"as <c>nvidia-drivers-173.14.15</c>. For these cards, you should mask\n"
"<c>>=x11-drivers/nvidia-drivers-174.00</c> in your\n"
"<path>/etc/portage/package.mask</path> file. This will prevent newer versions of\n"
"the driver which are incompatible with your card from being installed.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:85
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Old cards such as the GeForce 3 or GeForce 4 series require the 96.x drivers.\n"
"For these cards, you should mask <c>>=x11-drivers/nvidia-drivers-97.00</c> in\n"
"your <path>/etc/portage/package.mask</path> file.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:91
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The oldest NV2x-based cards (such as TNT, TNT2, GeForce, and GeForce 2) are no\n"
"longer supported by <c>nvidia-drivers</c>. Instead, use an open-source driver:\n"
"<c>xf86-video-nouveau</c> (recommended) or <c>xf86-video-nv</c> (old,\n"
"deprecated).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:98
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You can check for driver compatibility for your card at to determine which\n"
"driver supports it by viewing the README at its appropriate x86 or x86-64\n"
"<uri link=\"http://www.nvidia.com/object/unix.html\">release page</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:108
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configuring your Card"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:110
#, no-wrap
msgid "Kernel Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:114
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"As mentioned above, the nVidia kernel driver installs and runs against your\n"
"current kernel. It builds as a module, so it makes sense that your kernel must\n"
"support the loading of kernel modules. If you used <c>genkernel all</c> to\n"
"configure the kernel for you, then you're all set. If not, double check your\n"
"kernel configuration so that this support is enabled:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:121
#, no-wrap
msgid "Enabling the Loading of Kernel Modules"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:122
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Loadable module support ---&gt;\n"
"  [*] Enable loadable module support\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:127
#, no-wrap
msgid "You also need to enable <e>Memory Type Range Register</e> in your kernel:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:130
#, no-wrap
msgid "Enabling MTRR"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:131
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Processor and Features ---&gt;\n"
"  [*] MTRR (Memory Type Range Register) support\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:135
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" Also, if you have an AGP graphics card, you can optionally enable\n"
"<c>agpgart</c> support to your kernel, either compiled in or as a module. If\n"
"you do not use the in-kernel agpgart, then the drivers will use their own\n"
"<c>agpgart</c> implementation, called <c>NvAGP</c>.  On certain systems, this\n"
"performs better than the in-kernel agpgart, and on others, it performs worse.\n"
"You will need to evaluate this on your own system to get the best performance.\n"
"If you are unsure what to do, use the in-kernel agpgart:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:144
#, no-wrap
msgid "Enabling agpgart"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:145
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Device Drivers --->\n"
"Graphics Support --->\n"
"-*- /dev/agpgart (AGP Support) --->\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:151
#, no-wrap
msgid "On amd64, the IOMMU controls the agpgart setting.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:157
#, no-wrap
msgid "Arch-specific notes"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><impo>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:161
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"For x86 and AMD64 processors, the in-kernel driver conflicts with the binary\n"
"driver provided by nVidia. If you will be compiling your kernel for these CPUs,\n"
"you must completely remove support for the in-kernel driver as shown:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:166
#, no-wrap
msgid "Remove the in-kernel driver"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:167
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Device Drivers --->\n"
"Graphics Support --->\n"
"&lt;*&gt; Support for frame buffer devices --->\n"
"&lt; &gt;   nVidia Framebuffer Support\n"
"&lt; &gt;   nVidia Riva support\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:175
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"A framebuffer alternative is <c>uvesafb</c>, an <uri\n"
"link=\"http://dev.gentoo.org/~spock/projects/uvesafb/\">advanced\n"
"framebuffer</uri>. Note that you can choose to compile it into your kernel, or\n"
"as a module. The following example compiles uvesafb into the kernel.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:181
#, no-wrap
msgid "Enable uvesafb support"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:182
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Device Drivers --->\n"
"Graphics Support --->\n"
"&lt;*&gt; Support for frame buffer devices --->\n"
"&lt;*&gt;   Userspace VESA VGA graphics support\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:190
#, no-wrap
msgid "Or you can try <c>VESA</c>:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:193
#, no-wrap
msgid "Enable VESA support"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:194
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Device Drivers --->\n"
"Graphics Support --->\n"
"&lt;*&gt; Support for frame buffer devices --->\n"
"[*]   VESA VGA graphics support\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:202
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"For more information, you can look up the documentation for your chosen\n"
"framebuffer in <path>/usr/src/linux/Documentation/fb/</path>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:209
#, no-wrap
msgid "Continuing with Kernel Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:213
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The <c>nvidia-drivers</c> ebuild automatically discovers your kernel version\n"
"based on the <path>/usr/src/linux</path> symlink. Please ensure that you have\n"
"this symlink pointing to the correct sources and that your kernel is correctly\n"
"configured. Please refer to the \"Configuring the Kernel\" section of the <uri\n"
"link=\"/doc/en/handbook/\">Installation Handbook</uri> for details on configuring\n"
"your kernel.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:222
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"First, you'll need to choose the right kernel source using <c>eselect</c>. If\n"
"you are using <c>gentoo-sources-2.6.34-r1</c>, your kernel listing might look\n"
"something like this:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:227
#, no-wrap
msgid "Check your /usr/src/linux symlink"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:228
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>eselect kernel list</i>\n"
"Available kernel symlink targets:\n"
"  [1]   linux-2.6.34-gentoo-r1 *\n"
"  [2]   linux-2.6.33-gentoo-r2\n"
"  [3]   linux-2.6.32.9\n"
"<comment>(Verify that the right kernel is marked with an asterisk</comment>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:237
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"In the above output, you'll notice that the <c>linux-2.6.34-gentoo-r1</c> kernel\n"
"is marked with an asterisk (<b>*</b>) to show that it is the symlinked kernel.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:242
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If the symlink is not pointing to the correct sources, you must update the link\n"
"by selecting the number of your desired kernel sources, as in the example\n"
"above.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:247
#, no-wrap
msgid "Create/Update /usr/src/linux symlink"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:248
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(Select the correct kernel)</comment>\n"
"# <i>eselect kernel set 1</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:255
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing the Appropriate Drivers"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:259
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now it's time to install the drivers. You can do this by first following the\n"
"<uri link=\"/doc/en/xorg-config.xml\">X Server Configuration HOWTO</uri> and\n"
"setting <c>VIDEO_CARDS=\"nvidia\"</c> in <path>/etc/portage/make.conf</path>. When you\n"
"install the X server, it will then install the right version of\n"
"<c>nvidia-drivers</c> for you.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:267
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The drivers can be installed with the <c>gtk</c> USE flag set in\n"
"<path>/etc/portage/make.conf</path>. This will install\n"
"<c>media-video/nvidia-settings</c>, a handy graphical tool for monitoring and\n"
"configuring several aspects of your nVidia card.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><impo>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:274
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Every time you <uri link=\"/doc/en/kernel-upgrade.xml\">compile a new kernel</uri>\n"
"or recompile the current one, you will need to reinstall the nVidia kernel\n"
"modules. An easy way to keep track of modules installed by ebuilds (such as\n"
"<c>nvidia-drivers</c>) is to install <c>sys-kernel/module-rebuild</c>. Once\n"
"you've installed it, simply run <c>module-rebuild populate</c> to populate its\n"
"database with a list of packages to be rebuilt. Once you've finished compiling\n"
"or recompiling a kernel, just run <c>module-rebuild rebuild</c> to rebuild the\n"
"drivers for your new kernel.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:285
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Once the installation has finished, run <c>modprobe nvidia</c> to load the\n"
"kernel module into memory. If this is an upgrade, you should remove the\n"
"previous module first.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:290
#, no-wrap
msgid "Loading the kernel module"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:291
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>lsmod | grep nvidia &amp;&amp; rmmod nvidia</i>\n"
"# <i>modprobe nvidia</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:296
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To prevent you having to manually load the module on every bootup, you probably\n"
"want to have this done automatically each time you boot your system, so edit\n"
"<path>/etc/conf.d/modules</path> and add <c>nvidia</c> to it.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><impo>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:302
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you compiled <c>agpgart</c> as a module, you will need to add it to\n"
"<path>/etc/conf.d/modules</path> as well.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:309
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configuring the X Server"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:313
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Once the appropriate drivers are installed you need to configure your X Server\n"
"to use the <c>nvidia</c> driver instead of the default <c>nv</c> driver.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:318
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Open <path>/etc/X11/xorg.conf</path> with your favorite editor (such as\n"
"<c>nano</c> or <c>vim</c>) and go to the <c>Device</c> section. In that\n"
"section, change the <c>Driver</c> line:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:323
#, no-wrap
msgid "Changing nv to nvidia in the X Server configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:324
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Section \"Device\"\n"
"  Identifier \"nVidia Inc. GeForce2\"\n"
"  <i>Driver     \"nvidia\"</i>\n"
"  VideoRam   65536\n"
"EndSection\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:332
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Then go to the <c>Module</c> section and make sure the <c>glx</c> module gets\n"
"loaded while the <c>dri</c> module doesn't:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:336
#, no-wrap
msgid "Updating the Module section"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:337
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Section \"Module\"\n"
"  <comment>(...)</comment>\n"
"  <i># Load  \"dri\"\n"
"  Load  \"glx\"</i>\n"
"  <comment>(...)</comment>\n"
"EndSection\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:346
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Next, in section <c>Screen</c>, make sure that either the <c>DefaultDepth</c>\n"
"directive is set to 16 or 24, or that you only have <c>Display</c> subsections\n"
"with <c>Depth</c> settings of 16 or 24. Without it, the nVidia GLX extensions\n"
"will not start.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:352
#, no-wrap
msgid "Updating the Screen section"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:353
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Section \"Screen\"\n"
"  <comment>(...)</comment>\n"
"  <i>DefaultDepth 16</i>\n"
"  Subsection \"Display\"\n"
"  <comment>(...)</comment>\n"
"EndSection\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:362
#, no-wrap
msgid "Run <c>eselect</c> so that the X Server uses the nVidia GLX libraries:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:365
#, no-wrap
msgid "Running eselect"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:366
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>eselect opengl set nvidia</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:372
#, no-wrap
msgid "Adding your Users to the video Group"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:376
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You have to add your user to the <c>video</c> group so he has access to the\n"
"nVidia device files:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:380
#, no-wrap
msgid "Adding your user to the video group"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:381
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>gpasswd -a youruser video</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:385
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This might not be totally necessary if you aren't using <c>udev</c> but it\n"
"doesn't hurt either and makes your system future-proof.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:392
#, no-wrap
msgid "Testing your Card"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:396
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To test your nVidia card, fire up X and run <c>glxinfo</c>, which is part of the\n"
"<c>mesa-progs</c> package. It should say that direct rendering is activated:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:400
#, no-wrap
msgid "Checking the direct rendering status"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:401
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ <i>glxinfo | grep direct</i>\n"
"direct rendering: Yes\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:406
#, no-wrap
msgid "To monitor your FPS, run <c>glxgears</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:412
#, no-wrap
msgid "Enabling nvidia Support"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:416
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Some tools, such as <c>mplayer</c> and <c>xine-lib</c>, use a local USE flag\n"
"called <c>xvmc</c> which enables XvMCNVIDIA support, useful when watching high\n"
"resolution movies. Add in <c>xvmc</c> in your USE variable in\n"
"<path>/etc/portage/make.conf</path> or add it as USE flag to <c>media-video/mplayer</c>\n"
"and/or <c>media-libs/xine-lib</c> in <path>/etc/portage/package.use</path>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:424
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"There are also some applications that use the <c>nvidia</c> USE flag, so you\n"
"may want to add it to <path>/etc/portage/make.conf</path>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:429
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Then, run <c>emerge -uD --newuse world</c> to rebuild the applications that\n"
"benefit from the USE flag change.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:436
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using NVidia Settings Tool"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:440
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"nVidia also provides you with a settings tool. This tool allows you to monitor\n"
"and change graphical settings without restarting the X server and is available\n"
"through Portage as <c>media-video/nvidia-settings</c>. As mentioned earlier, it\n"
"will be pulled in automatically if you install the drivers with the <c>gtk</c>\n"
"USE flag set in <path>/etc/portage/make.conf</path> or in\n"
"<path>/etc/portage/package.use</path>.\n"
msgstr ""

