#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:455
#, no-wrap
msgid "Getting 2D to work on machines with 4Gb or more memory"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:459
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you are having troubles with the nVidia 2D acceleration it is likely that\n"
"you are unable to set up a write-combining range with MTRR. To verify, check\n"
"the contents of <path>/proc/mtrr</path>:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:464
#, no-wrap
msgid "Checking if you have write-combining enabled"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:465
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>cat /proc/mtrr</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:469
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Every line should contain \"write-back\" or \"write-combining\". If you see a line\n"
"with \"uncachable\" in it you will need to change a BIOS setting to fix this.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:474
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Reboot and enter the BIOS, then find the MTRR settings (probably under \"CPU\n"
"Settings\"). Change the setting from \"continuous\" to \"discrete\" and boot back\n"
"into Linux. You will now find out that there is no \"uncachable\" entry anymore\n"
"and 2D acceleration now works without any glitches.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:484
#, no-wrap
msgid "  When I attempt to load the kernel module I receive a \"no such device\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:489
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This usually occurs when you don't have a matching video card. Make sure that\n"
"you have an nVidia-powered graphical card (you can double-check this using\n"
"<c>lspci</c>).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:495
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you are confident that you have an nVidia card, check your BIOS and see if\n"
"the directive <e>Assign IRQ to VGA</e> is set.\n"
msgstr ""

