#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:522
#, no-wrap
msgid "Kernel module parameters"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:526
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The <c>nvidia</c> kernel module accepts a number of parameters (options) which\n"
"you can use to tweak the behaviour of the driver. Most of these are mentioned in\n"
"the documentation. To add or change the values of these parameters, edit the\n"
"file <c>/etc/modprobe.d/nvidia.conf</c>. Remember to run <c>update-modules</c> after\n"
"modifying this file, and bear in mind that you will need to reload the\n"
"<c>nvidia</c> module before the new settings take effect.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:534
#, no-wrap
msgid "Adjusting nvidia options"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:535
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(Edit /etc/modprobe.d/nvidia.conf in your favourite editor)</comment>\n"
"# <i>nano -w /etc/modprobe.d/nvidia.conf</i>\n"
"<comment>(Update module information)</comment>\n"
"# <i>update-modules</i>\n"
"<comment>(Unload the nvidia module...)</comment>\n"
"# <i>modprobe -r nvidia</i>\n"
"<comment>(...and load it once again)</comment>\n"
"# <i>modprobe nvidia</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:548
#, no-wrap
msgid "Advanced X configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:552
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The GLX layer also has a plethora of options which can be configured. These\n"
"control the configuration of TV out, dual displays, monitor frequency detection,\n"
"etc. Again, all of the available options are detailed in the documentation.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/nvidia-guide.xml:558
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you wish to use any of these options, you need to list them in the relevant\n"
"Device section of your X config file (usually <c>/etc/X11/xorg.conf</c>). For\n"
"example, suppose I wanted to disable the splash logo:\n"
